Dual License Model

This project adopts a Dual License Model:
1. Non-Commercial Use License (GNU Affero General Public License v3.0)

Unless otherwise specified, the source code of this project is released under the GNU AGPL v3.0 license, applicable to non-commercial use, defined as:

    "Use that is not intended for profit and does not directly or indirectly serve commercial interests."

This includes, but is not limited to:

    Personal learning or research;

    Internal use by non-profit organizations;

    Educational use in academic institutions;

    Open source community collaboration and exchange.

Under the terms of AGPL v3.0, users must retain attribution to the original authors and, if they modify or distribute the project, must also release the complete source code including all modifications. For full details, please refer to:
https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html
2. Commercial Use Requires Authorization

Any commercial use — including but not limited to the following — requires prior written authorization from the project maintainer:

    Use in profit-oriented products or services;

    Deployment, integration, or embedding in companies, institutions, or commercial teams;

    Providing services to clients, partners, or third parties;

    Any activities that directly or indirectly generate commercial value based on this project.

For inquiries, please contact: [ygz0523@foxmail.com]
3. License Policy Updates

The project maintainer reserves the right to update this license policy at any time as needed, including but not limited to:

    Refining the definition of commercial use;

    Adjusting thresholds based on user scale (e.g., individual, organization, team size);

    Modifying the authorization process or method.

All changes will be announced through official project channels (e.g., GitHub repository, official website). Users are responsible for reviewing the latest license policy before continuing to use the code.
